{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871045919,"sessionID":"ses_285d6bc34ffe3jO9hrpFbGwYjh","part":{"id":"prt_d7a29ac6c001KtvgUz0PJUN6Ir","messageID":"msg_d7a29a24c001e89CSYF8AP4i99","sessionID":"ses_285d6bc34ffe3jO9hrpFbGwYjh","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_2212d8fa35be475cadd91d23","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-029/delta-spec.md","limit":80},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-029/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-029 — SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the HTTP underlying client layer for the AgentCube Python SDK (AR-029). It focuses on session management, connection pooling, timeout handling, header management, and error handling for both control plane and data plane communications.\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-029\n10: - **Module**: `sdk-python`\n11: - **Language**: Python\n12: - **Size**: M\n13: - **Base Specs**: `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Background\n18: \n19: The AgentCube Python SDK uses HTTP for communication with both the Workload Manager (control plane) and the Router (data plane). This AR defines the HTTP client layer that handles:\n20: - Session management with connection pooling\n21: - Timeout configuration (connect and read timeouts)\n22: - Header management (Authorization, session IDs, Content-Type)\n23: - Request/response handling for different operation types\n24: - Error handling and exception conversion\n25: \n26: ---\n27: \n28: ## Requirements\n29: \n30: ### AR-029-001: HTTP Session 生命周期管理\n31: \n32: The system SHALL manage `requests.Session` lifecycle to ensure proper connection pooling and cleanup.\n33: \n34: #### Scenario: AR-029-001-A — Session creation with connection pooling\n35: \n36: - **GIVEN** `create_session(pool_connections=10, pool_maxsize=10)` is called\n37: - **WHEN** the function executes\n38: - **THEN** it SHALL return a `requests.Session` with `HTTPAdapter` mounted for both `http://` and `https://` schemes\n39: - **AND** the adapter SHALL have `pool_connections=10` and `pool_maxsize=10`\n40: \n41: #### Scenario: AR-029-001-B — Session context manager cleanup\n42: \n43: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterClient` or `AgentRuntimeClient` is used as a context manager\n44: - **WHEN** the `with` block exits normally\n45: - **THEN** the underlying `requests.Session` SHALL be closed via `.close()`\n46: - **AND** all HTTP connections SHALL be released back to the pool\n47: \n48: #### Scenario: AR-029-001-C — Session cleanup on exception\n49: \n50: - **GIVEN** an exception occurs within a context manager block\n51: - **WHEN** the `__exit__` method is called with exception info\n52: - **THEN** the session SHALL still be closed\n53: - **AND** the original exception SHALL be re-raised after cleanup\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: ### AR-029-002: HTTP 请求超时行为\n58: \n59: The system SHALL handle connect timeouts and read timeouts correctly for all HTTP operations.\n60: \n61: #### Scenario: AR-029-002-A — Connect timeout applies to all requests\n62: \n63: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` is initialized with `connect_timeout=5.0`\n64: - **WHEN** a request is made to an unreachable host\n65: - **THEN** a `requests.exceptions.ConnectTimeout` SHALL be raised within 5 seconds\n66: \n67: #### Scenario: AR-029-002-B — Read timeout for long-running operations\n68: \n69: - **GIVEN** `execute_command` is called with a command that takes longer than the read timeout\n70: - **WHEN** the server does not respond within `(connect_timeout + timeout)` seconds\n71: - **THEN** a `requests.exceptions.ReadTimeout` SHALL be raised\n72: \n73: #### Scenario: AR-029-002-C — Timeout tuple construction\n74: \n75: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.invoke` is called with default timeout settings\n76: - **WHEN** the request is prepared\n77: - **THEN** the `timeout` parameter SHALL be a tuple `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` where `connect_timeout` defaults to `5.0` and `timeout` defaults to `120`\n78: \n79: #### Scenario: AR-029-002-D — Per-call timeout override\n80: \n\n(Showing lines 1-80 of 427. Use offset=81 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-029 — SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the HTTP underlying client layer for the AgentCube Python SDK (AR-029). It focuses on session management, connection pooling, timeout handling, header management, and error handling for both control plane and data plane communications.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-029\n- **Module**: `sdk-python`\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n- **Base Specs**: `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe AgentCube Python SDK uses HTTP for communication with both the Workload Manager (control plane) and the Router (data plane). This AR defines the HTTP client layer that handles:\n- Session management with connection pooling","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-029/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775871045895,"end":1775871045917}}}}
